line_1: Let not neglect or distance e'er oppress,
line_2: Why should not fools the foolish thus caress;

line_2: Yes, he has lov'd to Transport's dire excess,

line_1: Bought of their prince a licence to oppress;
line_2: When those, prefer'd all grievance to redress,
So, when once the Son of Jess,
Whenever I am call'd to bless;

line_1: The pining sorrows which her soul oppress,
line_2: Her parents fond exulting heart to bless;

line_1: No more the powerful would the weak oppress,
line_2: But tyrants learn the luxury to bless;
